<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,512,847]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis box="[151,235,513,538]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Leaves</emphasis>
pinnae 4(3–7) per side of rachis. 
<emphasis box="[645,818,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Inflorescences</emphasis>
rachillae 4(2–6), 5.1(3.8–6.5) mm in diameter, not hairy, not filiform and not narrowed between the flower pits; proximal and distal lips drying the same color as the rachillae; triads mostly spirally arranged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,512,847]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,547,628,654]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
From 14°09’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[718,810,628,654]" degrees="15" direction="south" minutes="18" orientation="latitude" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" precision="925" value="-15.3">15°18’S</geoCoordinate>
and 39°00’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[967,1074,628,654]" degrees="39" direction="west" minutes="16" orientation="longitude" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" precision="925" value="-39.266666">39°16’W</geoCoordinate>
in the Atlantic Coastal Forest of 
<collectingCountry box="[182,254,666,692]" name="Brazil" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Brazil</collectingCountry>
in central 
<collectingRegion box="[378,447,666,692]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Bahia</collectingRegion>
at 212(45–380) m elevation in lowland tropical rainforest (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1231,666,692]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="130.[151,255,1715,1738]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,654,1671]" captionTargetId="figure@130.[151,1436,639,1689]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURE 35. Distribution maps of Geonoma pohliana subsp. rubescens, G. pohliana subsp. trinervis, G. pohliana subsp. unanensis, and G. pohliana subsp. weddelliana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3538432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3538432/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1437,512,847]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Labels of some specimens (e.g., 
<emphasis box="[631,1008,705,731]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Carvalho 6775, Noblick 4726</emphasis>
) describe the stems, leaves, and inflorescences as reddish-tinged. Some specimens (e.g., 
<emphasis box="[852,1014,744,770]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fiaschi 1051</emphasis>
), sympatric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" box="[1234,1429,744,770]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pohliana" subSpecies="unaensis">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1321,1429,745,770]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">unaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, exactly resemble that subspecies except for the non-hairy rachillae. The differences between the two subspecies are not clear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
